{
    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": "intro_elif_else",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Elif & Else",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Sometimes you need to check multiple conditions or handle what happens when none of your conditions are met. `elif` and `else` help you create more complex decision-making in your programs."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "else_statement",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "The `else` Statement",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The `else` statement runs code when the `if` condition is `False`. It's like saying \"if this doesn't happen, then do that instead.\""
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "age = 16\nif age >= 18:\n    print(\"You are an adult\")\nelse:\n    print(\"You are a minor\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "You are a minor"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "elif_statement",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "The `elif` Statement",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The `elif` statement (short for \"else if\") lets you check another condition if the first one is `False`."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "score = 75\nif score >= 90:\n    print(\"Excellent!\")\nelif score >= 70:\n    print(\"Not bad\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Keep trying\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Not bad"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "elif_statement",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can have multiple `elif` statements to check many conditions. Only the first `True` condition will run. If the first condition is `True`, the other `elif` statements will not be checked."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "score = 75\nif score >= 90:\n    print(\"Excellent!\")\nelif score >= 80:\n    print(\"Good job!\")\nelif score >= 70:\n    print(\"Not bad\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Keep trying\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Not bad"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "elif_else_order",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Python checks conditions in order: first `if`, then each `elif` from top to bottom, and finally `else` if none of the conditions are `True`. Only the first `True` condition runs."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "age = 25\nif age < 18:\n    print(\"Minor\")\nelif age < 65:\n    print(\"Adult\")\nelif age < 100:\n    print(\"Senior\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Centenarian\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Adult"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
